15 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Purpose. The legislature finds and declares that:
16 (1) the production of cattle constitutes a paramount industry in Montana that brings substantial
17 revenue to the state and provides consumers with local and nutritious beef;
18 (2) the production of cattle and beef provides a viable living for many Montanans and serves as
19 the economic foundation of many communities;
20 (3) the stabilization, maintenance, and expansion of markets for Montana cattle is necessary in
21 order to provide consumers with an adequate supply of high-quality beef;
22 (4) the committee form of administration is uniquely situated to provide those engaged in the
23 production of cattle with the opportunity to avail themselves of the benefits of collective action in advertising,
24 promotion, food safety production research, nutrition, marketing research, the collection and dissemination of
25 production and related statistics, and public education; and
26 (5) enabling the committee to formulate and effectuate research, promotion, and educational
27 programs designed to enhance the Montana cattle industry will create a favorable environment for Montana
